{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 09:24:55.126131", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nExecutive summary\\n- User access networks are not functional: both access hosts lack IPv4 addresses and cannot reach any services.\\n- The DHCP relays on the distribution routers are active, but the central DHCP server process is not running. This prevents lease assignment to the access hosts.\\n- The server farm (10.200.0.0/24), DNS, load balancer, and backend web segment are healthy and reachable among themselves.\\n\\nKey observations and evidence\\n1) Access hosts have no IP configuration\\n- host_1_1_1_1:\\n  - ip addr/ifconfig: eth0 has no IPv4; ip route is empty.\\n  - Ping and DNS tests fail with “Network is unreachable” (e.g., ping dns_server; dig @10.200.0.2).\\n- host_2_1_1_1:\\n  - ip addr/ifconfig: eth0 has no IPv4; ip route is empty.\\n  - Ping to dns_server fails with “Network is unreachable”.\\n\\n2) DHCP infrastructure status\\n- Distribution routers:\\n  - router_dist_1_1: dhcrelay present and listening (UDP 0.0.0.0:67, process 34/dhcrelay).\\n  - router_dist_2_1: dhcrelay present and listening (UDP 0.0.0.0:67, process 34/dhcrelay).\\n- Central DHCP server (dhcp_server 10.200.0.8):\\n  - isc-dhcp-server service state: inactive (dead).\\n  - No DHCP server process present; netstat shows no UDP/67 listening.\\n  - Network on server is fine (10.200.0.8/24 with default via 10.200.0.1).\\n\\n3) DNS service health (server farm)\\n- dns_server (10.200.0.2):\\n  - Listening on UDP 53 (10.200.0.2:53).\\n  - Local resolution works: dig @127.0.0.1 web99.local -> 10.200.0.7; web0.local -> 10.200.0.3.\\n  - HTTP from dns_server to web0.local and web99.local succeeds with normal timings.\\n- Access hosts cannot query DNS due to lack of IP connectivity, not due to DNS failure.\\n\\n4) Load balancer and backend segment\\n- load_balancer:\\n  - Interfaces: 10.200.0.7/24 (eth0), 20.200.0.1/24 (eth1); default route via 10.200.0.1.\\n  - Nginx listening on 0.0.0.0:80.\\n  - LB -> backend_web_0 (20.200.0.2) ping successful; backend path healthy.\\n- backend_web_0:\\n  - 20.200.0.2/24 with default via 20.200.0.1; interface up.\\n\\n5) Intra–server farm reachability\\n- Devices within 10.200.0.0/24 (dhcp_server, dns_server, load_balancer, web_server_*) can ping each other with low RTTs, indicating routing in the server area is healthy.\\n\\nDetected anomalies\\n- Access hosts are not obtaining DHCP leases (no IPv4 addresses, no routes).\\n- Central DHCP server service (isc-dhcp-server) is down/inactive; no DHCP listener on UDP/67.\\n\\nFault localization\\n- Faulty node: dhcp_server (10.200.0.8).\\n- Impacted domains: All access subnets (10.<core>.<dist>.0/24); end-to-end service from hosts to DNS and web services fails at L3 due to missing IP configuration.\\n\\nRoot cause\\n- The DHCP server process is not running on dhcp_server. Despite active DHCP relays on the distribution routers, there is no upstream server to reply to client DHCPDISCOVERs, resulting in host interfaces remaining unconfigured and “Network is unreachable” from the hosts. Other infrastructure (DNS, load balancer, backend network) is operational., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='3b81103d-b03b-485e-a8eb-60bc5bebb3d9'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
